1. On dev, update the version number to a release version without a dev component.
2. Update cff file release date and version (dropping dev component).
3. Consolidate inst/NEWS.Rd and run make.
4. Commit changes to DESCRIPTION, codemeta.json, news files and docs.
5. Checkout master (git checkout master).
6. Merge changes (git merge dev) and resolve conflicts, if any, and commit.
7. Check winbuilder (`devtools::check_win_devel()`) and rhub (`devtools::check_rhub()`).
8. Update and commit cran-comments.md.
9. Release (`devtools::release()`) and wait for CRAN response.
10. Once CRAN version goes online (news file in particular) rebuild pkgdown docs, commit changes and CRAN-RELEASE file, and push.
11. On GitHub, tag as new release and copy NEWS.md updates.
12. Remove CRAN-RELEASE and then commit.
13. Checkout dev (`git checkout dev`).
14. Merge master (`git merge master`).
15. Add dev component to version number, update cff, news and docs, commit and push.
